---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContentPage from '../components/ContentPage.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Betting Education — Odds, Hold, Fair Odds, EV & ROI | Fight Prophet"
  description="Learn the exact betting math Fight Prophet shows: American odds, implied probability, sportsbook hold, fair (devigged) odds, expected value, ROI, edge, and parlays — plus a live odds calculator."
>
  <ContentPage
    eyebrow="Betting Education"
    title="Betting Education"
    intro="Plain-English explanations of the exact betting math shown across Fight Prophet — and a live odds calculator that uses the same formulas as our backend. Educational only, not betting advice."
    updated="June 26, 2026"
  >
    <section>
      <h2>1. American Odds</h2>
      <p>
        American odds describe a bet relative to a <b>$100 stake</b>.
        <b>Positive</b> odds (e.g. <code>+150</code>) are an underdog: a $100 stake wins
        <code>$150</code> profit. <b>Negative</b> odds (e.g. <code>-200</code>) are a favourite:
        you must stake <code>$200</code> to win <code>$100</code> profit.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Positive: profit on $100 = the odds value (<code>+150</code> → $150).</li>
        <li>Negative: profit on $100 = <code>10000 / |odds|</code> (<code>-200</code> → $50).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Implied Probability</h2>
      <p>Every price implies a win probability. That is the break-even win rate for the bet.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Positive odds: <code>p = 100 / (odds + 100)</code></li>
        <li>Negative odds: <code>p = |odds| / (|odds| + 100)</code></li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Add up both fighters' implied probabilities and you will get <i>more</i> than 100% —
        that extra is the sportsbook's built-in margin (the hold).
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Sportsbook Hold</h2>
      <p>
        The <b>hold</b> (a.k.a. vig or overround) is how the book makes money. For a two-way
        fight market it is simply how far the two implied probabilities sum above 100%:
      </p>
      <p><code>hold = fighter_implied + opponent_implied - 1</code></p>
      <p>
        We colour it <span class="fp-pos">green</span> below 3%, <span class="fp-warn">yellow</span> from
        3–6%, and <span class="fp-neg">red</span> above 6%. Lower hold means a fairer market and more
        of your edge survives. If we only have one side's odds, hold is shown as “—”.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Fair Odds (Devigging)</h2>
      <p>
        <b>Devigging</b> removes the hold so both sides sum to exactly 100%. The result is the
        market's <b>fair probability</b> — its honest opinion with the margin stripped out:
      </p>
      <p><code>fair_prob = side_implied / (fighter_implied + opponent_implied)</code></p>
      <p>Convert that fair probability back to a price to get <b>fair odds</b>:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>p &lt; 0.5</code>: <code>fair = 100 · (1 - p) / p</code></li>
        <li><code>p &gt; 0.5</code>: <code>fair = -100 · p / (1 - p)</code></li>
        <li><code>p = 0.5</code>: <code>+100</code></li>
      </ul>
      <p>Fair probability differs from raw market probability precisely by the hold.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Expected Value (EV)</h2>
      <p>
        EV is the average profit per bet if you could replay the fight many times, using the
        <b>model's</b> probability and a $100 stake:
      </p>
      <p><code>EV = (model_prob · profit) − ((1 − model_prob) · 100)</code></p>
      <ul>
        <li><b>Positive EV</b>: the price pays more than your probability says it should — a good bet long term.</li>
        <li><b>Negative EV</b>: the price is too short — a bad bet long term.</li>
        <li>A +EV bet can still lose a single fight; a −EV bet can still win one. EV is about the long run, not one result.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. ROI</h2>
      <p>We use standard bettor ROI: return per dollar staked.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><b>Expected ROI</b> (before the fight): <code>EV / stake</code>. With a $100 stake, <code>ROI = EV / 100</code>.</li>
        <li><b>Realized ROI</b> (after results): the actual return on settled picks — win returns <code>decimal − 1</code> per unit, a loss returns <code>−1</code>. You'll see this on the Events History page once a fight closes.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not headline volume-adjusted ROI; the user-facing number is per-dollar ROI.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Edge</h2>
      <p>Edge is the key value signal — how much higher the model rates a side than the fair market:</p>
      <p><code>edge = model_prob − fair_prob</code></p>
      <p>
        Comparing against <i>fair</i> probability (not the raw price) means edge is not just an
        artifact of the hold — it reflects genuine disagreement with the de-vigged market.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>8. Parlays</h2>
      <p>A parlay needs every leg to win, so probabilities multiply:</p>
      <p><code>parlay_prob = p₁ · p₂ · … · pₙ</code></p>
      <p>
        Each extra leg shrinks your probability fast, which is why parlays are hard to beat and
        why sportsbooks promote them — the hold compounds across legs. Fair parlay odds come from
        converting the combined probability back to a price; the sportsbook payout is the product
        of each leg's decimal odds.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="fp-calc-wrap">
      <h2>Fight odds calculator</h2>
      <p class="fp-calc-sub">Enter both fighters' American odds — everything else is worked out for you, live, with the same formulas as our backend (<code>betting_math.py</code>). Educational only.</p>

      <datalist id="odds-suggestions">
        <option value="-300"></option><option value="-250"></option><option value="-200"></option>
        <option value="-175"></option><option value="-150"></option><option value="-130"></option>
        <option value="-120"></option><option value="-110"></option><option value="100"></option>
        <option value="110"></option><option value="120"></option><option value="130"></option>
        <option value="150"></option><option value="175"></option><option value="200"></option>
        <option value="250"></option><option value="300"></option>
      </datalist>

      <div class="fp-calc fp-calc-hero">
        <div class="fp-calc-row">
          <div class="fp-calc-field">
            <label for="oa">Fighter A odds</label>
            <input type="number" id="oa" value="-150" step="5" inputmode="numeric" list="odds-suggestions" placeholder="e.g. -150" />
          </div>
          <div class="fp-calc-field">
            <label for="ob">Fighter B odds</label>
            <input type="number" id="ob" value="+130" step="5" inputmode="numeric" list="odds-suggestions" placeholder="e.g. +130" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="fp-calc-result"><span>Sportsbook hold (margin)</span><b id="r-hold">—</b></div>

        <div class="fp-calc-sides">
          <div class="fp-side">
            <div class="fp-side-name">Fighter A</div>
            <div class="fp-side-line"><span>Implied</span><b id="r-a-imp">—</b></div>
            <div class="fp-side-line"><span>Fair (no-vig)</span><b id="r-a-fair">—</b></div>
            <div class="fp-side-line"><span>Fair odds</span><b id="r-a-fairodds">—</b></div>
          </div>
          <div class="fp-side">
            <div class="fp-side-name">Fighter B</div>
            <div class="fp-side-line"><span>Implied</span><b id="r-b-imp">—</b></div>
            <div class="fp-side-line"><span>Fair (no-vig)</span><b id="r-b-fair">—</b></div>
            <div class="fp-side-line"><span>Fair odds</span><b id="r-b-fairodds">—</b></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="fp-calc-q">Implied = the price's break-even win rate (includes the book's margin). Fair = the same with the hold removed, so both sides add to 100%. Leave a field blank and hold/fair can't be computed.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </ContentPage>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  // Plain <script> (no type="module") so Astro bundles it and resolves the
  // betting-math.mjs import at build time. With type="module" Astro leaves it
  // inline and the relative import 404s in the browser.
  import * as bm from '../lib/betting-math.mjs';

  const $ = (id) => document.getElementById(id);
  const n = (el) => (el && el.value !== '' ? Number(el.value) : NaN);
  const pct = (v) => (Number.isFinite(v) ? `${(Math.round(v * 1000) / 10).toFixed(1)}%` : '—');
  const odds = (v) => (Number.isFinite(v) ? (v > 0 ? `+${Math.round(v)}` : String(Math.round(v))) : '—');

  function recompute() {
    const a = n($('oa'));
    const b = n($('ob'));
    const pa = bm.impliedProbFromAmerican(a);
    const pb = bm.impliedProbFromAmerican(b);

    // hold (needs both sides) — colour by threshold
    const hold = bm.marketHold(pa, pb);
    const holdEl = $('r-hold');
    holdEl.textContent = pct(hold);
    holdEl.classList.remove('fp-pos', 'fp-neg', 'fp-warn');
    const lbl = bm.holdLabel(hold);
    if (lbl) holdEl.classList.add(lbl === 'low' ? 'fp-pos' : lbl === 'medium' ? 'fp-warn' : 'fp-neg');

    // per-side implied + fair (devig needs both sides)
    $('r-a-imp').textContent = pct(pa);
    $('r-b-imp').textContent = pct(pb);
    const fairA = bm.devigFairProb(pa, pa, pb);
    const fairB = bm.devigFairProb(pb, pa, pb);
    $('r-a-fair').textContent = pct(fairA);
    $('r-b-fair').textContent = pct(fairB);
    $('r-a-fairodds').textContent = odds(bm.fairAmericanOdds(fairA));
    $('r-b-fairodds').textContent = odds(bm.fairAmericanOdds(fairB));
  }

  document.querySelectorAll('.fp-calc input').forEach((el) => el.addEventListener('input', recompute));
  recompute();
</script>

<style>
  .fp-content-body code { font-size: 0.92em; }
  .fp-pos { color: #16a34a; }
  .fp-neg { color: #dc2626; }
  .fp-warn { color: #b45309; }

  .fp-calc-sub { opacity: 0.7; margin-top: -0.3rem; }
  .fp-calc {
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.15rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    align-content: start;
  }
  .fp-calc-hero { max-width: 560px; margin-top: 0.4rem; }
  .fp-calc-q { margin: 0.1rem 0 0; font-size: 0.78rem; opacity: 0.65; line-height: 1.4; }
  .fp-calc-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.7rem; }
  .fp-calc-field { display: grid; gap: 0.3rem; }
  .fp-calc-field label {
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  .fp-calc input {
    font: inherit;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.7rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22);
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.02);
    color: inherit;
    width: 100%;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }
  .fp-calc input:focus { outline: 2px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.45); outline-offset: 1px; }
  /* prominent hold result */
  .fp-calc-result {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    padding-top: 0.6rem;
    border-top: 1px dashed rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.14);
  }
  .fp-calc-result span { font-size: 0.82rem; opacity: 0.7; }
  .fp-calc-result b { font-size: 1.6rem; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; line-height: 1; }
  /* per-side breakdown */
  .fp-calc-sides { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.7rem; }
  .fp-side {
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.7rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.3rem;
  }
  .fp-side-name { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; opacity: 0.85; }
  .fp-side-line { display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .fp-side-line span { font-size: 0.74rem; opacity: 0.62; }
  .fp-side-line b { font-size: 1rem; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    .fp-calc { border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.14); }
    .fp-calc input { border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.22); background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03); }
    .fp-calc-result { border-top-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.18); }
    .fp-side { border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12); }
    .fp-warn { color: #eab308; }
  }
</style>
